JOHANNESBURG - Sixteen people were injured on Friday morning when a bakkie and a taxi collided on Christiaan De Wet Road in Constantia Kloof, west of Johannesburg, ER24 paramedics said.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics had found the taxi on the side of the road against a barrier.[CONSTANTIA KLOOF] - Taxi and bake collie leaving 16 injured. https://t.co/MzMb2y6vyu @eNCA @_ArriveAlive @FatalMoves pic.twitter.com/p4yifXxH2c The bakkie was found parked in the middle of the road. Several passengers from the taxi were found walking around on the scene. Meiring said that on closer inspection, paramedics found two men lying trapped inside the front of the taxi.IN PICS: Motorists warned to be careful on wet roads ER24 paramedics, along with provincial services, used specialised rescue tools to free both men from the vehicle ... both men had sustained numerous injuries and were in a critical condition, he said.READ: 16 killed in taxi crash, 6 children among themFourteen other patients had injuries ranging in severity from minor to moderate.The critically injured patients were treated with advanced life-support equipment. Once treated, the patients were transported to various hospitals for further treatment, Meiring said.The cause of the collision was not immediately known but local authorities attended the scene to investigate.Africa News Agency